Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with information transmission over a wiretap channel and uses lattice coding techniques. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on achieving secure communication by using artificial noise and full-duplex devices. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a communication scenario involving a network relay and a base station, which falls under the domain of networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and analysis of a communication system involving multiple devices, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve the transmission of multimedia content over the wiretap channel, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
